				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well, Florida is one of the states that has claimed to have doctors "fleeing en masse" due to the outrageous cost of malpractice insurance. They are also one of the states claiming the reason for the steep hike in insurance premiums are because of frivolous med-mal suits, and the high number of those kinds of suits. But, the numbers speak diferently. there are more doctors applying for licenses and practicing medicine in the state of Florida than last year.
<br />

<br />
Strangely enough, when the people who made the claims that insurance premiums were at an all time high because of claims paid in med-mal cases voluntarily came to testify under oath, thier story changed completely. Funny what the threat of perjury will do to an individual's statement.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
