Well of course. An increase in claims can result is an increased number of lawsuits. An increased number of lawsuits can result in an increase in doctor errors. An increase in award can result in an increase of expenses, which happens in every single profession on the planet. Medical care itself has become increasingly more expensive over the years, and medical procedures have become more pricey with newer procedures and better technology. What's your point?
