This is the problem, it doesn’t matter what’s causing the increase. That it is, is causing a problem. Do you think passing a law that says from now on all doctors must be better at their jobs is going to be a viable solution? What do you propose?
<br />

<br />
I don’t think there is an increasing problem with doctor skill, I think there is an increase problem with people forgiving honest mistakes. Not just in this industry, but in many of them. If a doctor did his best and your child was damaged for life, people used to be willing to accept that so long as the doctor did his best. Now, if your child is damaged, someone has got pay for it, no matter what. That’s the attitude.
